{"questionId":"5275558","questionHtml":"<p>The intensity pattern of monochromatic light of wavelength λ, is projected onto a screen.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/32e6f28f63e40b3b5466ba3ee41a35a76e36fc51.png\"></p>\n<p>What combination produces this pattern?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width:346px;height:179px;border-color:#000000;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height:29px;\">\n<td style=\"width:45px;height:29px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width:128.117px;height:29px;text-align:center;\"><strong>Number of slits</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:143.883px;height:29px;text-align:center;\"><strong>Width of slits<br></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px;\">\n<td style=\"width:45px;height:29px;\">A.</td>\n<td style=\"width:128.117px;height:29px;text-align:center;\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width:143.883px;height:29px;text-align:center;\">smaller than λ</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:45px;\">B.</td>\n<td style=\"width:128.117px;text-align:center;\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width:143.883px;text-align:center;\">greater than λ</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px;\">\n<td style=\"width:45px;height:29px;\">C.</td>\n<td style=\"width:128.117px;height:29px;text-align:center;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width:143.883px;height:29px;text-align:center;\">smaller than λ</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px;\">\n<td style=\"width:45px;height:29px;\">D.</td>\n<td style=\"width:128.117px;height:29px;text-align:center;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width:143.883px;height:29px;text-align:center;\">greater than λ</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"5275558","referenceCode":"23M.1.HL.TZ1.27","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"The intensity pattern of monochromatic light of wavelength λ, is projected onto a screen. What combination produces this pattern? Number of slits Width of slits A. 1 smaller than λ","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"27","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}